headline.main: Second Front'; Britain Attacks in Libya

lead_paragraph: Rain fell in the hour before the Egyptian dawn. The sandy desert turned into brown and sticky paste, but in the wet darkness hushed infantrymen were boarding trucks and from camouflaged shelters planes of the R.A.F., waiting for leather helmeted pilots, were being trundled.
abstract: Sen O'Mahoney rites aid of U S-built weapons in Libyan campaign
